290
00:16:21,300 --> 00:16:21,980
Just one.

291
00:16:22,380 --> 00:16:22,780
Sure.

292
00:16:27,740 --> 00:16:29,180
I hope the taste hasn't changed.

293
00:16:29,780 --> 00:16:31,020
Of course. You can try it.

294
00:16:31,380 --> 00:16:31,900
Thanks.

295
00:16:37,700 --> 00:16:39,540
Let's check in on the traffic now.

296
00:16:39,900 --> 00:16:41,260
There's a two-car rear-end collision

297
00:16:41,260 --> 00:16:43,340
on Hantang Road heading southbound,

298
00:16:43,700 --> 00:16:45,980
causing slow-moving traffic
in the section.

299
00:16:46,260 --> 00:16:48,860
Please drive carefully
if you're passing through.

300
00:17:03,460 --> 00:17:03,980
Right here is fine.

301
00:17:04,100 --> 00:17:04,340
Okay.

302
00:17:16,500 --> 00:17:18,340
That piano of yours
really does need replacing.

303
00:17:18,580 --> 00:17:20,260
Poor tuning can affect
a player's ear, after all.

304
00:17:22,220 --> 00:17:22,900
Sorry

305
00:17:23,340 --> 00:17:24,500
to have taken up your time

306
00:17:25,300 --> 00:17:26,380
and made you come so far.

307
00:17:27,180 --> 00:17:28,660
Don't be so formal with me.

308
00:17:28,660 --> 00:17:30,620
I'm the professional
when it comes to pianos.

309
00:17:30,780 --> 00:17:31,820
Happy to give you some advice.

310
00:17:32,500 --> 00:17:32,780
Right.

311
00:17:33,460 --> 00:17:34,220
Thank you for your help.

312
00:17:34,660 --> 00:17:35,300
No problem.

313
00:17:39,380 --> 00:17:40,220
Excuse me.

314
00:17:40,220 --> 00:17:40,820
Sorry.

315
00:19:16,860 --> 00:19:17,460
Excuse me.

316
00:19:20,140 --> 00:19:20,580
Hello.

317
00:19:21,060 --> 00:19:21,820
I'm sorry.

318
00:19:22,060 --> 00:19:22,460
Is this yours?

319
00:19:23,860 --> 00:19:24,140
Here.

320
00:19:24,620 --> 00:19:25,220
Thank you.

321
00:19:25,540 --> 00:19:26,780
No problem. Keep it safe.

322
00:20:06,500 --> 00:20:07,940
What kind of piano

323
00:20:07,980 --> 00:20:09,580
are you looking for?

324
00:20:09,820 --> 00:20:12,220
We have both upright and grand pianos.

325
00:20:12,260 --> 00:20:13,340
We can help you find the right one.

326
00:20:16,900 --> 00:20:19,180
Do you have the Yamaha YM50?

327
00:20:19,180 --> 00:20:19,740
Yes.

328
00:20:19,740 --> 00:20:20,780
Right this way, please.

329
00:20:21,100 --> 00:20:21,340
Okay.

330
00:20:21,500 --> 00:20:22,540
May I ask

331
00:20:22,540 --> 00:20:23,860
how old your child is?

332
00:20:26,660 --> 00:20:27,340
Starting middle school soon.

333
00:20:27,620 --> 00:20:28,020
Alright.

334
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:30,460
Look, this is the model.

335
00:20:31,180 --> 00:20:31,860
This one right here.

336
00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:35,580
May I try it?

337
00:20:35,700 --> 00:20:36,540
Of course.

338
00:20:36,540 --> 00:20:37,980
Just a moment. Let me adjust it for you.

339
00:20:38,100 --> 00:20:38,380
Okay.

340
00:20:41,460 --> 00:20:42,020
What do you think...?

341
00:20:45,700 --> 00:20:46,580
What's up

342
00:20:46,980 --> 00:20:47,940
with you today?

343
00:20:48,300 --> 00:20:49,260
You seem off.

344
00:20:49,300 --> 00:20:50,540
Like your mind is somewhere else.

345
00:20:53,860 --> 00:20:54,500
Then

346
00:20:55,340 --> 00:20:56,540
I'd better go find it.

347
00:20:57,420 --> 00:20:58,540
Alright. Please give it a try.

348
00:20:59,140 --> 00:20:59,460
Okay.

349
00:21:00,340 --> 00:21:00,700
Excuse me.

350
00:21:00,980 --> 00:21:01,260
Sure.

351
00:21:01,580 --> 00:21:01,980
Thank you.

352
00:21:22,700 --> 00:21:23,460
The high notes are bright,

353
00:21:23,500 --> 00:21:24,620
and the bass is rich and full.

354
00:21:25,500 --> 00:21:26,460
You play beautifully.

355
00:21:26,500 --> 00:21:27,660
You must be an expert.

356
00:21:29,580 --> 00:21:30,220
Then

357
00:21:30,860 --> 00:21:31,580
we'll take this one.

358
00:21:32,780 --> 00:21:33,700
Here's the thing, sir.

359
00:21:33,700 --> 00:21:34,660
This piano

360
00:21:34,700 --> 00:21:35,980
comes with a matching bench.

361
00:21:36,700 --> 00:21:38,980
Could you tell me
how tall your child is?

362
00:21:40,020 --> 00:21:40,580
About

363
00:21:41,580 --> 00:21:42,060
this high.

364
00:21:42,340 --> 00:21:42,940
One meter forty-nine.

365
00:21:44,140 --> 00:21:45,460
Mom always knows best.

366
00:21:45,700 --> 00:21:45,980
Alright.

367
00:21:46,020 --> 00:21:47,860
Please wait in the lounge area.

368
00:21:48,420 --> 00:21:49,900
I'll check our warehouse stock.

369
00:21:50,420 --> 00:21:51,500
Okay. Thank you.

370
00:21:59,100 --> 00:22:00,460
Mr. Feng, since winning the award,

371
00:22:00,780 --> 00:22:02,140
have you been busier than before?

372
00:22:04,780 --> 00:22:05,740
It should be a good thing.

373
00:22:06,340 --> 00:22:09,260
Just worried I'll have
even less time for Le.

374
00:22:10,780 --> 00:22:12,380
You and your mom
are both career-focused.

375
00:22:12,820 --> 00:22:13,340
But it's okay.

376
00:22:13,700 --> 00:22:14,420
Le is very understanding.

377
00:22:16,380 --> 00:22:17,660
But what I said last time

378
00:22:17,700 --> 00:22:18,940
wasn't just being polite.

379
00:22:19,100 --> 00:22:20,420
If you and your mom are busy,

380
00:22:20,620 --> 00:22:21,220
you can really

381
00:22:21,260 --> 00:22:22,700
leave Le with me after school.

382
00:22:23,540 --> 00:22:24,780
He's starting middle school.

383
00:22:24,780 --> 00:22:26,020
He can take care of himself.

384
00:22:26,540 --> 00:22:28,820
You two even sound the same.

385
00:22:30,300 --> 00:22:32,020
But meals shouldn't be rushed.

386
00:22:32,540 --> 00:22:33,740
He can't always just order takeout.

387
00:22:34,380 --> 00:22:35,580
I usually eat alone.

388
00:22:35,860 --> 00:22:37,220
Having Le over would mean

389
00:22:37,300 --> 00:22:38,060
we could cook more dishes.

390
00:22:38,580 --> 00:22:39,940
But that's too much trouble for you.

391
00:22:40,940 --> 00:22:41,980
Don't be so formal with me.

392
00:22:57,220 --> 00:22:58,700
You always like meeting me here.

393
00:23:00,100 --> 00:23:00,660
Because

394
00:23:01,100 --> 00:23:02,060
I love this street.

395
00:23:02,500 --> 00:23:04,020
It always has a special feel to it.

396
00:23:05,940 --> 00:23:07,700
You sound like an old man.

397
00:23:08,060 --> 00:23:08,820
So profound.

398
00:23:10,260 --> 00:23:11,300
Maybe I've been drinking too much tea.

399
00:23:11,700 --> 00:23:12,460
What do you feel like eating later?

400
00:23:13,780 --> 00:23:14,460
Hotpot?

401
00:23:15,540 --> 00:23:15,860
Sure.

402
00:23:17,380 --> 00:23:19,220
But I know a place
that does amazing skewers.

403
00:23:20,300 --> 00:23:21,300
Alright. Your call.

404
00:23:21,780 --> 00:23:22,100
Okay.

405
00:23:22,340 --> 00:23:23,180
Then let's have skewers.

406
00:23:44,720 --> 00:23:53,120
[Chengdu]

407
00:24:06,200 --> 00:24:10,360
[Cygne]

408
00:24:18,100 --> 00:24:18,740
Someday,

409
00:24:19,460 --> 00:24:20,940
I'll open a winery here,

410
00:24:21,060 --> 00:24:22,460
and you can open
a dance studio downstairs.

411
00:24:22,460 --> 00:24:23,860
[Jiabao Dance Studio]

412
00:24:23,860 --> 00:24:24,220
What do you think?

413
00:24:26,100 --> 00:24:26,620
Sure.

414
00:24:27,540 --> 00:24:28,500
It suits you.

415
00:24:29,220 --> 00:24:31,260
After a drink, we can perform

416
00:24:31,780 --> 00:24:32,460
a drunken fist dance.

417
00:24:32,500 --> 00:24:33,260
Drunken fist?

418
00:24:34,580 --> 00:24:34,980
Good.

419
00:24:36,860 --> 00:24:38,060
What should I

420
00:24:38,060 --> 00:24:38,940
name the winery?

421
00:24:40,980 --> 00:24:41,620
Cygne.

422
00:24:48,980 --> 00:24:54,460
[Cygne]

423
00:24:54,460 --> 00:24:55,260
Welcome to come again.

424
00:24:58,580 --> 00:24:59,980
Are you here for a wine tasting?

425
00:25:01,540 --> 00:25:03,700
How long have you been open?

426
00:25:04,300 --> 00:25:05,420
Over six years.

427
00:25:06,620 --> 00:25:08,060
Let me give you a quick introduction.

428
00:25:08,460 --> 00:25:09,020
Thank you.

429
00:25:09,860 --> 00:25:10,980
Cygne Winery

430
00:25:10,980 --> 00:25:12,660
produces and sells its own wine.

431
00:25:13,220 --> 00:25:14,100
Most wineries

432
00:25:14,100 --> 00:25:15,860
deal in wines from around the world.

433
00:25:16,180 --> 00:25:17,260
But Cygne Winery

434
00:25:17,540 --> 00:25:18,940
owns its own vineyards

435
00:25:18,940 --> 00:25:19,900
and production facility.

436
00:25:20,900 --> 00:25:22,580
Our owner is a true wine connoisseur.

437
00:25:23,340 --> 00:25:24,620
He's dedicated

438
00:25:24,620 --> 00:25:26,140
to creating wines
that suit the Chinese palate.

439
00:25:26,860 --> 00:25:29,020
That's how the Cygne brand was born.

440
00:25:31,260 --> 00:25:31,820
Our

441
00:25:31,820 --> 00:25:34,580
dry red and dry white
are the most popular.

442
00:25:35,300 --> 00:25:36,420
Would you like to try some?

443
00:25:39,340 --> 00:25:39,820
Sir.

444
00:25:50,420 --> 00:25:51,500
So you're the one who opened this.

445
00:25:53,060 --> 00:25:53,860
Surprised?

446
00:26:02,340 --> 00:26:03,620
You probably could have guessed.

447
00:26:15,420 --> 00:26:15,700
Here.

448
00:26:16,340 --> 00:26:16,740
Try it.

449
00:26:17,060 --> 00:26:17,580
Thank you.

450
00:26:31,660 --> 00:26:32,340
If you like it,

451
00:26:32,620 --> 00:26:33,340
I can give you a couple of bottles.

452
00:26:34,420 --> 00:26:34,820
Thanks.

453
00:26:36,500 --> 00:26:37,100
How have you been?

454
00:26:39,860 --> 00:26:40,500
What do you think?

455
00:26:43,060 --> 00:26:44,460
Looks like you're doing pretty well.

456
00:26:46,100 --> 00:26:47,460
And you fulfilled your dream

457
00:26:49,300 --> 00:26:50,100
on this very street.

458
00:26:51,900 --> 00:26:53,500
Because the rent here is not expensive.

459
00:26:57,540 --> 00:26:57,940
And you?

460
00:26:58,580 --> 00:26:59,380
You're not dancing anymore?

461
00:27:09,420 --> 00:27:09,980
Is it good?

462
00:27:13,540 --> 00:27:14,580
Distinct graininess.

463
00:27:16,780 --> 00:27:18,300
The floral notes appear briefly,

464
00:27:18,300 --> 00:27:19,020
and then recede quickly.

465
00:27:19,580 --> 00:27:20,220
A sharp, bold retreat.

466
00:27:23,140 --> 00:27:24,260
A sharp, bold retreat.

467
00:27:28,020 --> 00:27:29,260
First time I've heard that comment.

468
00:27:29,860 --> 00:27:30,820
It's quite accurate.

469
00:27:31,780 --> 00:27:33,420
Well, I know about making a bold retreat.

470
00:27:34,580 --> 00:27:36,140
I've been drifting alone
out there for so long.

471
00:27:40,540 --> 00:27:41,260
So you came back?

472
00:27:44,820 --> 00:27:45,820
It's good to settle down.

473
00:27:49,020 --> 00:27:50,140
What are your plans
now that you're back?

474
00:27:52,020 --> 00:27:52,300
Actually...

475
00:27:52,300 --> 00:27:52,620
Dad!

476
00:27:53,140 --> 00:27:53,860
I'm here.

477
00:27:58,140 --> 00:27:58,780
Sorry about that.

478
00:27:58,780 --> 00:27:59,300
Hello, ma'am.

479
00:27:59,620 --> 00:28:00,820
I didn't know you had a guest.

480
00:28:00,940 --> 00:28:01,900
Should I take Le and go...?

481
00:28:01,900 --> 00:28:02,420
No need.

482
00:28:02,660 --> 00:28:04,060
We were just finishing up.

483
00:28:04,060 --> 00:28:04,780
I should get going.

484
00:28:04,940 --> 00:28:05,940
Let me introduce you.

485
00:28:06,260 --> 00:28:07,300
My friend, Tan Siting.

486
00:28:08,020 --> 00:28:08,620
This is...

487
00:28:08,620 --> 00:28:09,660
Hello, I'm Wen Peiyan.

488
00:28:10,100 --> 00:28:10,580
Hello.

489
00:28:11,860 --> 00:28:13,260
I won't disturb you any further.

490
00:28:13,580 --> 00:28:14,180
I'm leaving.

491
00:28:14,340 --> 00:28:14,740
Wait.

492
00:28:24,180 --> 00:28:24,540
Here.

493
00:28:24,700 --> 00:28:25,380
I promised you this.

494
00:28:26,140 --> 00:28:26,620
Thank you.

495
00:28:26,820 --> 00:28:27,140
Bye.

496
00:28:27,700 --> 00:28:28,380
Bye, ma'am.

497
00:28:34,940 --> 00:28:35,940
What are you doing here?

498
00:28:36,020 --> 00:28:36,980
Didn't your grandma pick you up?

499
00:28:37,540 --> 00:28:38,860
She just called.

500
00:28:38,860 --> 00:28:40,020
Something came up at the office,

501
00:28:40,020 --> 00:28:41,660
so she asked me to bring Le to you.

502
00:28:43,500 --> 00:28:43,860
Dad,

503
00:28:44,220 --> 00:28:45,740
thanks for the piano.

504
00:28:46,300 --> 00:28:47,700
Ms. Wen told me all about it.

505
00:28:47,980 --> 00:28:50,100
You came all this way just to say that?

506
00:28:51,700 --> 00:28:52,980
As long as you practice hard,

507
00:28:53,180 --> 00:28:54,380
this is all I'm supposed to do.

508
00:28:55,340 --> 00:28:55,860
Thank you.

509
00:28:56,700 --> 00:28:58,460
He still has his piano lesson
this afternoon, right?

510
00:28:59,180 --> 00:28:59,420
Yes.

511
00:28:59,460 --> 00:29:00,260
I'll drive you back.

512
00:29:16,980 --> 00:29:18,700
Do you prefer a black or brown piano?

513
00:29:19,580 --> 00:29:20,140
White.

514
00:29:20,900 --> 00:29:21,660
White?

515
00:29:22,420 --> 00:29:24,100
Your answers are always
full of surprises.

516
00:29:24,700 --> 00:29:25,740
I give you two choices,

517
00:29:25,740 --> 00:29:26,940
and you always pick a third.

518
00:29:28,100 --> 00:29:28,540
Feng Rui,

519
00:29:28,780 --> 00:29:29,940
black or brown?

520
00:29:31,660 --> 00:29:32,540
I bet

521
00:29:32,700 --> 00:29:34,660
he'd pick white.

522
00:29:34,780 --> 00:29:35,300
Le,

523
00:29:35,740 --> 00:29:37,180
your dad also chose white.

524
00:29:37,180 --> 00:29:38,340
You like white that much, huh?

525
00:29:38,860 --> 00:29:39,300
Okay.

526
00:29:39,300 --> 00:29:39,980
White it is.

527
00:29:40,940 --> 00:29:42,060
What do you feel like eating later?

528
00:29:42,900 --> 00:29:43,660
I feel like

529
00:29:43,660 --> 00:29:44,300
having a burger.

530
00:30:17,380 --> 00:30:17,820
Where are you headed?

531
00:30:17,980 --> 00:30:18,500
I'll give you a ride.

532
00:30:20,500 --> 00:30:21,140
It's you?

533
00:30:40,900 --> 00:30:41,300
Here.

534
00:30:48,660 --> 00:30:48,980
Is it okay?

535
00:30:49,940 --> 00:30:50,300
Yes.

536
00:30:57,900 --> 00:30:58,580
To the theater.

537
00:30:59,380 --> 00:30:59,780
Alright.

538
00:31:00,580 --> 00:31:01,780
I'll pay for the gas.

539
00:31:04,180 --> 00:31:04,580
Don't worry about it.

540
00:31:06,020 --> 00:31:06,580
No, I have to.

541
00:31:06,860 --> 00:31:07,740
Let's keep things clear.

542
00:31:09,060 --> 00:31:10,300
Honestly, I didn't expect

543
00:31:10,300 --> 00:31:11,340
to run into you again today.

544
00:31:12,500 --> 00:31:13,420
You seem to be in a hurry.

545
00:31:14,020 --> 00:31:15,700
You're a student
at the Dance Academy, right?

546
00:31:16,660 --> 00:31:17,460
How do you know?

547
00:31:18,300 --> 00:31:19,900
Our company is right across
from your school.

548
00:31:20,220 --> 00:31:21,780
I pass by your gate every day.

549
00:31:22,020 --> 00:31:23,020
No wonder it's such a coincidence.

550
00:31:24,900 --> 00:31:26,900
You weren't hoping to find
a pair of ballet shoes, were you?

551
00:31:28,580 --> 00:31:30,420
Well, you've helped me twice now.

552
00:31:30,940 --> 00:31:32,420
I still don't know your name

553
00:31:32,420 --> 00:31:33,340
or what you do.

554
00:31:34,020 --> 00:31:34,900
Is it okay to ask?

555
00:31:35,460 --> 00:31:36,380
Of... Of course.

556
00:31:36,380 --> 00:31:37,260
My name is Feng Rui.

557
00:31:37,460 --> 00:31:38,940
Our company deals in wine.

558
00:31:40,140 --> 00:31:42,460
Are you performing
at the theater this time?

559
00:31:43,540 --> 00:31:44,340
An audition.

560
00:31:44,900 --> 00:31:45,820
Queen Ballet is recruiting.

561
00:31:47,020 --> 00:31:47,460
What Ballet?

562
00:31:48,060 --> 00:31:48,620
Queen Ballet.

563
00:31:49,180 --> 00:31:51,620
London's Queen Ballet.

564
00:31:52,460 --> 00:31:53,740
We just call it Queen Ballet.

565
00:31:54,340 --> 00:31:55,340
Will you make it in time?

566
00:31:55,580 --> 00:31:56,660
Yes. Don't worry.

567
00:32:06,220 --> 00:32:07,300
Go on, we're here.

568
00:32:07,420 --> 00:32:07,820
Thank you.

569
00:32:08,540 --> 00:32:09,180
Hope we are not too late.

570
00:32:10,420 --> 00:32:10,780
Bye.

571
00:32:10,820 --> 00:32:11,100
Bye.

572
00:32:27,180 --> 00:32:28,380
Madam, I'm sorry.

573
00:32:28,780 --> 00:32:29,300
I'm late.

574
00:32:29,300 --> 00:32:30,140
Take this away.

575
00:32:30,820 --> 00:32:31,220
I'm sorry.

576
00:32:31,220 --> 00:32:32,380
We're already finished.

577
00:32:33,060 --> 00:32:33,660
Madam...

578
00:32:35,540 --> 00:32:35,980
No?

579
00:32:36,140 --> 00:32:36,580
No one.

580
00:32:54,980 --> 00:32:56,180
Is there one more student?

581
00:32:58,620 --> 00:32:59,700
She's late.

582
00:33:37,000 --> 00:33:42,940
♪If a tsunami roared inside my heart♪

583
00:33:43,740 --> 00:33:49,140
♪Who among the passersby
would hear the wind?♪

584
00:33:50,180 --> 00:33:51,180
Yes. Very good.

585
00:33:51,180 --> 00:33:54,020
♪I never dared to hope, yet you came by♪

586
00:33:54,020 --> 00:33:54,580
Okay.

587
00:33:57,220 --> 00:33:58,700
♪And listened to my hesitant life♪

588
00:33:58,700 --> 00:33:59,940
You did well today.

589
00:34:00,300 --> 00:34:02,420
Same time next week

590
00:34:03,020 --> 00:34:04,020
for the second round here.

591
00:34:04,700 --> 00:34:05,340
Don't be late.

592
00:34:05,820 --> 00:34:06,700
Thank you, Madam.

593
00:34:06,700 --> 00:34:09,620
♪How rare it is in life
to have someone to like?♪

594
00:34:10,460 --> 00:34:14,500
♪How rare it is for liking
to become favor?♪

595
00:34:14,500 --> 00:34:15,380
I'm so sorry.

596
00:34:15,620 --> 00:34:16,940
I left my things in your car again.

597
00:34:17,460 --> 00:34:19,100
♪How rare it is for favor
to reunite again?♪

598
00:34:19,100 --> 00:34:20,580
You sew your own shoes?

599
00:34:20,900 --> 00:34:22,420
We all sew our own shoes.

600
00:34:22,940 --> 00:34:23,940
Only we ourselves know

601
00:34:23,940 --> 00:34:25,620
what kind of shoes fit
and work best for us.

602
00:34:26,900 --> 00:34:28,860
I basically need a new pair
every five days.

603
00:34:29,460 --> 00:34:30,220
You go through shoes that fast?

604
00:34:32,500 --> 00:34:34,340
Dance practice must be very tough.

605
00:34:34,940 --> 00:34:35,460
It's alright.

606
00:34:36,340 --> 00:34:37,380
When you love it, it doesn't feel tough.

607
00:34:38,020 --> 00:34:38,460
Let's go.

608
00:34:38,900 --> 00:34:39,300
Go.

609
00:34:39,300 --> 00:34:41,180
♪It teaches us how precious devotion is♪

610
00:34:41,180 --> 00:34:41,940
I'll leave then.

611
00:34:42,380 --> 00:34:42,940
Well,

612
00:34:44,860 --> 00:34:46,340
can we exchange phone numbers?

613
00:34:48,140 --> 00:34:48,580
Sure.

614
00:34:48,580 --> 00:34:51,460
♪To give a lifetime for a single name♪

615
00:34:52,660 --> 00:34:57,260
♪If it were you, I'd do the same♪

616
00:35:03,720 --> 00:35:18,000
[Cygne]

617
00:35:38,060 --> 00:35:38,820
Look.

618
00:35:41,780 --> 00:35:44,060
They get along so well.

619
00:35:57,340 --> 00:35:59,340
How did the piano shopping
go for you two?

620
00:36:03,140 --> 00:36:04,220
Peiyan

621
00:36:05,420 --> 00:36:06,500
was a huge help.

622
00:36:07,820 --> 00:36:08,460
She has great taste.

623
00:36:09,500 --> 00:36:10,340
Of course.

624
00:36:10,820 --> 00:36:12,220
She definitely has good taste.

625
00:36:18,580 --> 00:36:19,380
Peiyan

626
00:36:20,420 --> 00:36:21,220
is well-educated,

627
00:36:21,460 --> 00:36:22,500
graceful, and dignified.

628
00:36:23,420 --> 00:36:24,500
The most important thing is

629
00:36:25,380 --> 00:36:26,260
that she's so good to Le.

630
00:36:29,300 --> 00:36:29,940
Rui,

631
00:36:30,660 --> 00:36:31,860
you should appreciate that.

632
00:36:35,340 --> 00:36:35,940
Mom,

633
00:36:36,620 --> 00:36:39,620
I mean Peiyan
is professional about music

634
00:36:39,620 --> 00:36:40,860
and is a great teacher.

635
00:36:41,660 --> 00:36:42,100
Don't go.

636
00:36:44,220 --> 00:36:45,300
It's almost time.

637
00:36:45,300 --> 00:36:46,260
Slice some apples for them

638
00:36:46,460 --> 00:36:47,540
for some vitamin C.

639
00:36:49,220 --> 00:36:49,500
Coming.

640
00:36:49,500 --> 00:36:49,780
Grandma.

641
00:36:50,260 --> 00:36:50,700
Look.

642
00:36:51,300 --> 00:36:53,820
Mr. Feng specially prepared
these apples for you.

643
00:36:55,420 --> 00:36:55,740
Here.

644
00:36:55,900 --> 00:36:56,540
Thank you, Grandma.

645
00:36:56,980 --> 00:36:58,420
Peiyan, thank you for your hard work.

646
00:36:58,820 --> 00:36:59,460
Not at all.

647
00:36:59,460 --> 00:37:00,500
Le is the one working hard.
Have some more.

648
00:37:00,780 --> 00:37:01,500
Eat up.

649
00:37:03,220 --> 00:37:04,700
Any plans later?

650
00:37:05,580 --> 00:37:06,060
No.

651
00:37:06,300 --> 00:37:07,620
Then come shopping with me.

652
00:37:08,420 --> 00:37:09,780
Just the two of us. Without them.

653
00:37:12,100 --> 00:37:13,020
No problem.

654
00:37:29,020 --> 00:37:30,500
I think we should

655
00:37:30,620 --> 00:37:31,740
buy those shoes.

656
00:37:32,700 --> 00:37:33,740
Madam, that's enough.

657
00:37:33,860 --> 00:37:35,220
We haven't been shopping long,

658
00:37:35,220 --> 00:37:37,140
and you've already bought Le
two pairs of shoes.

659
00:37:38,140 --> 00:37:39,500
Besides, kids at his age

660
00:37:39,500 --> 00:37:40,740
outgrow shoes so fast.

661
00:37:40,740 --> 00:37:41,140
It's enough.

662
00:37:42,660 --> 00:37:43,980
Yes, I know.

663
00:37:44,780 --> 00:37:46,420
You shouldn't spoil a child.

664
00:37:46,940 --> 00:37:47,780
I know that.

665
00:37:48,540 --> 00:37:49,540
But

666
00:37:50,180 --> 00:37:52,500
I just can't help myself.

667
00:37:53,500 --> 00:37:55,260
But those shoes really are quite nice.

668
00:37:56,820 --> 00:37:58,180
You're right. They are nice.

669
00:37:59,260 --> 00:38:01,340
Maybe you could think
about it a bit more

670
00:38:01,460 --> 00:38:01,980
before deciding?

671
00:38:04,740 --> 00:38:05,940
Let's sit down for a while.

672
00:38:05,940 --> 00:38:06,420
Sure.

673
00:38:06,580 --> 00:38:07,700
Let's go over there.

674
00:38:13,020 --> 00:38:15,460
What do you think of Rui?

675
00:38:19,740 --> 00:38:20,620
He's a good man.

676
00:38:20,860 --> 00:38:21,820
And we get along well.

677
00:38:22,420 --> 00:38:23,900
Just seeing

678
00:38:24,660 --> 00:38:25,740
how much he loves Le shows

679
00:38:25,940 --> 00:38:27,140
how responsible he is.

680
00:38:28,140 --> 00:38:30,100
Once, Le joked with me,

681
00:38:30,980 --> 00:38:34,180
saying "If my dad ended up with Ms. Wen,

682
00:38:34,740 --> 00:38:37,660
I'd be totally happy."

683
00:38:41,180 --> 00:38:43,100
Le really likes you.

684
00:38:44,460 --> 00:38:45,500
He talks about you all the time.

685
00:38:47,620 --> 00:38:48,660
I also hope

686
00:38:49,820 --> 00:38:50,700
that one day,

687
00:38:51,820 --> 00:38:53,540
you and Rui might be together.

688
00:38:54,500 --> 00:38:55,060
That'd be wonderful.

689
00:39:02,020 --> 00:39:02,660
Madam,

690
00:39:03,340 --> 00:39:04,700
I understand what you're saying.

691
00:39:06,780 --> 00:39:08,060
Let me be honest with you.

692
00:39:09,980 --> 00:39:12,020
Actually, I have feelings for Rui.

693
00:39:12,980 --> 00:39:13,940
I've also wondered

694
00:39:14,700 --> 00:39:17,900
if we could take the next step.

695
00:39:20,700 --> 00:39:21,620
But it always feels like

696
00:39:22,260 --> 00:39:23,460
he's overly formal with me.

697
00:39:23,460 --> 00:39:25,540
It's like he keeps me at a distance.

698
00:39:27,460 --> 00:39:28,940
You've got the wrong idea.

699
00:39:29,220 --> 00:39:30,180
That's just how he is.

700
00:39:30,820 --> 00:39:34,140
He doesn't treat me
and his dad the same way.

701
00:39:35,060 --> 00:39:35,780
He treats his dad

702
00:39:36,620 --> 00:39:37,820
like a friend.

703
00:39:38,300 --> 00:39:40,180
He'd tell him everything.

704
00:39:40,860 --> 00:39:41,660
I have to admit,

705
00:39:43,420 --> 00:39:44,140
I'm a bit jealous

706
00:39:44,300 --> 00:39:45,620
of his dad over it.

707
00:39:46,060 --> 00:39:46,780
Thank you, Madam.

708
00:39:47,420 --> 00:39:48,580
Have some more cake.

709
00:39:48,580 --> 00:39:48,940
Okay.

710
00:39:53,740 --> 00:39:54,380
Madam,

711
00:39:56,580 --> 00:39:57,700
what was

712
00:39:58,220 --> 00:39:59,660
Le's mom really like?

713
00:40:11,340 --> 00:40:12,340
Back then,

714
00:40:13,100 --> 00:40:14,460
they were so young.

715
00:40:16,340 --> 00:40:17,300
They were only thinking

716
00:40:19,100 --> 00:40:20,140
about themselves,

717
00:40:21,340 --> 00:40:22,580
with no idea

718
00:40:23,580 --> 00:40:24,780
what real life was about.

719
00:40:29,420 --> 00:40:31,180
What's past is past.

720
00:40:31,180 --> 00:40:32,460
No need to bring it up.

721
00:40:33,860 --> 00:40:35,460
We always have to look forward,

722
00:40:36,180 --> 00:40:36,700
right?

723
00:40:37,820 --> 00:40:38,300
Right.

724
00:40:39,340 --> 00:40:39,860
Actually,

725
00:40:40,020 --> 00:40:41,460
no matter which direction you look,

726
00:40:41,980 --> 00:40:42,900
it's always forward.

727
00:40:45,100 --> 00:40:45,660
Peiyan,

728
00:40:47,380 --> 00:40:49,780
your words really put my mind at ease.

729
00:40:51,180 --> 00:40:51,900
I think

730
00:40:52,460 --> 00:40:53,220
you could be

731
00:40:53,460 --> 00:40:54,460
a bit more proactive.

732
00:40:55,540 --> 00:40:56,700
I'm here for you.

733
00:40:56,940 --> 00:40:58,180
Whenever you need me,

734
00:40:58,580 --> 00:40:59,380
I'll help you.

735
00:41:01,580 --> 00:41:02,380
I understand, Madam.

736
00:41:12,060 --> 00:41:12,740
Gao Hui.

737
00:41:14,180 --> 00:41:15,580
You must've been waiting
a long time for this.

738
00:41:15,820 --> 00:41:16,620
Leave Rui.

739
00:41:17,020 --> 00:41:17,580
You murderer!

740
00:41:17,580 --> 00:41:17,900
Get out!

741
00:41:17,900 --> 00:41:18,940
Mom, stop making a scene.

742
00:41:18,940 --> 00:41:20,660
I want him to see

743
00:41:20,660 --> 00:41:21,540
what his good mother

744
00:41:21,540 --> 00:41:23,020
has done to him.

745
00:41:23,020 --> 00:41:24,420
Tan Siting?

746
00:41:24,420 --> 00:41:26,980
Our family will never accept her.

747
00:41:28,300 --> 00:41:31,060
She and Rui will break up.

748
00:41:31,700 --> 00:41:35,180
♪The day understands
the night's dark hue♪

749
00:41:36,700 --> 00:41:43,060
♪With waiting, it spins
through the beginning and end♪

750
00:41:45,260 --> 00:41:48,740
♪Who says that time is relative?♪

751
00:41:50,500 --> 00:41:56,380
♪When you love, it's absolute♪

752
00:41:58,700 --> 00:42:02,100
♪Absolute tolerance♪

753
00:42:02,100 --> 00:42:05,220
♪For the years' long cruelty♪

754
00:42:05,620 --> 00:42:10,420
♪Let my remaining days
remember one soul♪

755
00:42:11,140 --> 00:42:14,580
♪Let me return to your side♪

756
00:42:14,580 --> 00:42:17,820
♪To dance for you once more♪

757
00:42:18,300 --> 00:42:21,900
♪I'll keep spinning, spinning for you♪

758
00:42:21,900 --> 00:42:24,780
♪Until longing makes me dizzy♪

759
00:42:24,900 --> 00:42:27,860
♪Let me love you once again♪

760
00:42:28,180 --> 00:42:31,460
♪To dance for you once more♪

761
00:42:32,100 --> 00:42:35,060
♪Like a song entwining meetings
and farewells♪

762
00:42:35,060 --> 00:42:38,340
♪Spinning and spinning again♪

763
00:42:50,420 --> 00:42:53,380
♪Let me love you once again♪

764
00:42:53,860 --> 00:42:56,980
♪To dance for you once more♪

765
00:42:57,780 --> 00:43:00,580
♪Like a song entwining days and nights♪

766
00:43:00,580 --> 00:43:03,380
♪Spinning and spinning again♪

767
00:43:05,020 --> 00:43:07,860
♪A spinning dance♪

768
00:43:08,460 --> 00:43:11,140
♪Yet to love you is to love your world♪

769
00:43:11,140 --> 00:43:17,620
♪We might as well be lost
in this obsession♪

770
00:43:18,660 --> 00:43:21,500
♪A long and winding detour♪

771
00:43:22,220 --> 00:43:25,140
♪Love looks back at every turn♪

772
00:43:25,140 --> 00:43:28,100
♪Like a song entwining meetings
and farewells♪

773
00:43:28,100 --> 00:43:30,860
♪Spinning and spinning again♪

774
00:43:30,860 --> 00:43:35,780
♪Until forever♪
